Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: autodata
Version: 0.12
Summary: Auto allocation dict and list
Home-page: https://github.com/shii4c/PythonAutoData
Author: Kenichiro SHII
Author-email: shii4c@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: Python AutoData
        ================
        
        Overview
        ----------
        
        This is auto allocate dict and list like Perl.
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
          import autodata
        
          d = autodata.autodict()
          d["key1"]["key2"] = "val" # => d["key1"] == {"key2": "val"}
          d["key2"] += 1            # => d["key2"] == 1
          d["key3"][2] = 1          # => d["key3"] == [None, None, 1]
        
        
        Restriction
        -------------
        
        - The type of dict key is only strings.
        - Dict item is not allocated by dict.get method.
        - None value is not returned by autolist[number]. Instead, an emptyitem object is returned.
        
        Known issues
        --------------
        
        .. code-block:: python
        
          d = autodata.autodict()
          a = d["key"]
          a += 1  # => d == {"key" : 1}
          a += 1  # => d == {"key" : 1}
        
